## Early game

**Cervantes** on Earth (Sabotage) has the wiki's only documented Detonite
Ampule drop table: a Rotation B resource cache with roughly a 12.2% chance.
Detonite Ampule has no enemy drop table, so this quick Sabotage — clear the
tileset, grab the Rotation B cache, reset — is the clearest way to farm it
early.

## Mid & late game

**Piscinas** on Saturn (Dark Sector Survival) is the wiki's recommended
endgame spot, run with a Steel Path squad for longer rotations than a
standalone Sabotage reset allows. Detonite Ampule is still a resource-cache
pickup rather than an enemy drop, so Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel
Path passive don't raise the odds per cache — the payoff here is simply more
survival rotations, and therefore more caches, per hour.

